	<Title>
		Are your lamps bright enough?
	</Title>
	<Body>
		&lt;p&gt; When you turn on the lights, make sure they&apos;re getting the job done. Concentrate light on close work by using adjustable gooseneck lamps and lights underneath kitchen cabinets. The finer your task, the more light you need. Position lights for reading to shine from over your shoulder. Use lampshades that completely shield the bulb so that light is directed up and down, not into your eyes.&lt;/p&gt;
	</Body>
